column38: ["1;You remember. Man, he was a pain.;You remember. You really liked him back then.","2;Hug him for a long moment.;Shake his hand instead.","3;“Yup. We should catch up! How about dinner soon?”;“Yup. It’s been a while. I’m still getting settled.”","4;Try to follow him, but it’s too late.;Turn around - you’re curious to see who he’s talking about.","5;Can’t help it. You like her immediately.;Get Chris’ point. The girl seems like a jerk.","6;You really don’t want to be late but reluctantly agree to grab coffee.;“I can’t - gotta go. Maybe tomorrow.”","7;Nod and wait for him to invite you to his table. ;Point to an empty seat. “Sit here, save me the table.”","8;“So, what’s the deal with Maya? Catch me up!\";Continue looking at your phone.","9;Ask for his other favorite spots around town - you need some recommendations.;Space out and try to sort out your plans for the afternoon.","10;“Thanks - but I’m still working on this one.” (You like your current coffee) ;You still have most of your coffee left but you order the new one instead.","11;Feel happy to see a familiar face and move a bit closer. ;Feel uncomfortable and move away slightly. ","12;“It’s just because she knows my cousin.”;“You owe me now.”","13;“Oh – sure… I’ll move your bag to the trunk.” (Unfasten seatbelt and move bag to the trunk);“Oh yeah. Move your bag to the trunk.”","14;Wait for Chris to take the middle seat.;Immediately move over to the middle seat.","15;“Hi, nice to meet you.”;“Hello, nice meeting you.”","16;“She knew me when we were younger.”;“She knows my cousin.”","17;Change the subject. (How can he talk like that?);Nod while giving him a reassuring look. (You feel bad for him)","18;“I’m good wherever. Maya, where do you think I should sit?”;“Actually, I was going to sit there.” (Take the seat)","19;“Mrs. Newcomb, I heard you have some issues in the office. How is that going…?”; “So, Nancy, how is Keith? What is he up to these days?”","20;“Give them a call and schedule a meeting, please.”;Go to the website on your phone.","21;“Thanks - but I already have so many references. I’ll definitely reach out if I need more.”;(Slightly uncomfortably) \"Ok… great.\"","22;You don’t feel like it but you were about to go check out that room anyway.; “Ok, wait for me there, Mrs. Newcomb – I will meet you in a bit.”","23;“Yes – she told me some things… But I’d rather keep it between her and I.”;“Yes – she told me some funny stories from back in the day, and told me to tell you she misses you, Nancy.”","24;“It’s ok - I’m fine standing.” ;There is a lot of clutter. You move it and sit like she told you.","25;“We can leave in 30 minutes.”;“Whenever - it’s up to you.”","26;Wait to see if Maya offers you a ride home.;“Let’s go, Maya. You’re driving me home.”","27;You don’t want to get between them, so you change the subject.;“He said a few things…” (Tell her everything Chris told you).","28;(take a seat next to Maya) “I’d love to hear your idea!”;Sit across the table and change the topic.","29;“I’m good here. Grab a chair and join us.”;Sit where he directed you.","30;Smile politely and wait to introduce yourself.;Stand aside while they talk and check your text messages.","31;“I’ll wait to hear from you, sir.”;“Let’s just schedule now. How’s Monday, 9 a.m.?”","32;“No, I’ll wait.”;“I’ll take a coffee, made fresh. I appreciate it.”","33;(On your way out) \"Tell Hayworth I’m free Wednesday morning.”;(Slightly bothered) “Fine, I’ll wait.”","34;(Check your email on your phone) “Is it always that hectic in here?”;“Looks like you’re the real person running this place - everybody really relies on you!” ","35;“I think that’s pretty common, actually.”;“Wow, they must really value you to have kept you that long!” ","36;“Yes, it’s much nicer than yesterday.”;“Now I understand why you call this place Green-ville.”","37;Wave back at her to come join you.;You’re annoyed at having to walk over there, but you do.","38;“Take this - make sure it’s in the proposal.\";“This is part of chapter 3.”","39;(Are bored) “Is anyone else joining for dinner?” Try to make small talk.;Want to get to know Kayce. “So, do you have family here, Kayce?”","40;“Absolutely, we have a lot to talk about.”;“I’ll try but I have a lot going on right now.”","41;(Glad he asked) Tell him everything you’ve been through in the last few weeks.;“I’m still trying to make it work.”","42;Ask about his favorite things about Hayworth Industries.;Study the menu to decide what you want to eat, without replying.","43;It’s not what you wanted, but it’s already ordered.;(Talking to the waiter) “I’ll actually have that last special instead.” ","44;(You’re bored with the conversation) \"You work with everyone, huh?\";“You seem to get along with everyone in the community.” ","45;(You nervously change the subject) “The food is great here.”; (Laughing) “Oh yes, especially Mrs. Newcomb...”","46;“I really need this job. It’s been really tough.”;“I’m interested, but I have other offers.”","47;Smile and hug her back.;Go for a handshake instead.","48;“How’s your business idea coming? Any more meetings with Mrs. Newcomb?”;“Damn, I’m tired. I just wanna finish my food and go home.”","49;(Waving at her to come over) “Kayce, this is Maya. You are welcome to join us.”;Turn away to avoid her, but she spots you and comes over to say hi.","50;“The waiter will come by in a minute.”;“Do you know Kayce? Hayworth’s assistant?” (Tell Maya about Kayce)","51;(Laughing) “Don’t be ridiculous!”;(Moving away) “Don’t be ridiculous.\"","52;This is not in your job description, but you’ll do it anyway. ;“I’m sorry, but I can’t make it – I already have another meeting scheduled. Maybe Kayce can do it?” ","53;Work hard, but you prefer to stick to the hiring contract and don’t stay overtime.;Reluctantly stay overtime.","54;“Yeah, I knew I would nail it.” ;“I would never get it without someone pulling some strings.”","55;“Yes – I am excited to work on these projects with you!”;“We’ll see. First I have a lot to work on.”","56;“Oh - okay. I suppose I’ll get to work on those now, then.”;“Start with these. My assistant will give you the rest tomorrow.”","57;(Don’t want to get involved) “I’ll give you privacy. I think we’re done, anyway.”;(Feel concerned) “Everything alright, Nancy? What is it?”","58;(Reach out to hold her shoulder) “Oh no, I’m so sorry.”;“Ok - we’ll continue later.” ","59;Grab one of the ads and put in your pocket.;“Send me the terms. I’ll have my assistant take a look.” ","60;“Can we talk about that later? Now I need you to help me get some documents signed.”;Slightly annoyed, you take a look at the document.","61;“Let me know when you have some more information.”;“Get me the contract and floor plan and tell them you need ’til tomorrow.”","62;“I can’t, maybe just leave it here and do it tomorrow?” ;You hate when she bosses you around, but drop off the dry cleaning anyway.","63;“Thanks for the offer, Kayce, but I am actually going to rent from Nancy.”;“Let’s live together. I think we would be great housemates.”"]

column137: Friend I already knew. Seems like a pretty good and loyal friend, but maybe does not treat women well, seeing as he called Maya crazy and ran away from her. I have a feeling the situation was more complex than that
column138: Domineering to those she views as her equal or lesser, but is very eager to please her superiors, such as Newcomb. Creative but doesn't stand up for herself enough due to embarrassment.
column139: Mysterious, hard-working woman who started at the bottom and worked her way up. Attractive and commands a room when she walks in. Very private but ultimately kind
column140: Rich guy, probably has some sort of big secret. Acts fake and does not care much about anything but appearances
column141: Hardworking but taken advantage of by Hayworth. Bosses me around but only because she is frustrated with Hayworth overworking her
column142: Arrogant, interested in bettering himself only, maybe selfish. Friendly enough, though.

column430: I thought it was fun. It was fast paced and the mystery aspect kept me engaged. I also liked making up my own opinions about each character and choosing how to treat them. I also really liked the character design; it felt appropriately modern and made it more relatable.
column431: I wish the characters were slightly more likable. Additionally, it felt like some of the plot/relationships were vague and confusing, for example my cousin Jennifer.
